$ /mnt

The `/mnt` directory is used for (temporary) mount points.

The → Windows/Subsystem-for-Linux[Windows Subsystem for Linux] mounts Windows Drives (`C:\` etc.) to `/mnt/c` etc.

sa:

 `→ Linux/fhs/media`

 Two → Windows/Subsystem-for-Linux directories found under `/mnt` are → Linux/fhs/mnt/wsl[`wsl`] and → Linux/fhs/mnt/wslg[`wslg`].

 `→ Linux/shell/commands/mount`
